HEADWORD: Prittle-prattle
<hw>Prit"tle-prat`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Prattle</er>.]</ety> <def>Empty talk; trifling loquacity; prattle;
-- used in contempt or ridicule.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Abp. Bramhall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

